116
00:06:07,230 --> 00:06:09,491
And so the average purchase was looking like $500.

117
00:06:09,812 --> 00:06:13,234
And that was immediately obvious, like this is wrong.

118
00:06:13,734 --> 00:06:17,397
And we were able to isolate it and get rid of it.

119
00:06:17,677 --> 00:06:20,139
But a lot of times, data issues are much more subtle.

120
00:06:24,835 --> 00:06:27,577
different things not firing in the tutorial sequence, or

121
00:06:27,757 --> 00:06:31,059
weird client timestamps that are changing dates, and other

122
00:06:31,520 --> 00:06:32,420
little subtle things.

123
00:06:32,821 --> 00:06:34,622
So one of the things that I think is really important is

124
00:06:34,642 --> 00:06:37,744
that you should never rely on a single analytic system, and

125
00:06:37,764 --> 00:06:40,246
you should never rely on an analytic system where you

126
00:06:40,326 --> 00:06:42,827
can't get in and inspect the individual records.

127
00:06:43,147 --> 00:06:45,709
Because oftentimes, you need to see the individual little

128
00:06:45,889 --> 00:06:49,232
items to find problems and figure out what they are.

129
00:06:51,102 --> 00:06:54,443
Even when your data is good and when the data is correct,

130
00:06:54,563 --> 00:06:55,564
it can be misleading.

131
00:06:57,424 --> 00:07:00,465
This looks like four separate pictures

