00:07:00,525 --> 00:07:03,567
photoshopped together to create an appealing color grid, right?

133
00:07:06,348 --> 00:07:06,628
Wrong.

134
00:07:07,228 --> 00:07:08,828
And data is like this.

135
00:07:09,229 --> 00:07:13,270
A lot of times, something appears one way,

136
00:07:13,390 --> 00:07:15,591
very straightforward when you look at it in one direction.

137
00:07:15,911 --> 00:07:17,771
But if you change the angle, you can

138
00:07:17,811 --> 00:07:19,752
see that it's really something completely different.

139
00:07:21,248 --> 00:07:24,510
Here's an example of that happening from congregate.com

140
00:07:24,530 --> 00:07:24,810
data.

